// Code-signing configuration for local builds.
//
// This repository ships with an EMPTY DEVELOPMENT_TEAM so it carries no
// personal Apple Developer identity. To build a signed app (device install,
// distribution, or notarization) set your own Team ID.
//
// Two options:
//   1. Xcode UI — open the generated project and pick your team under
//      "Signing & Capabilities" (Xcode writes to the local, gitignored project).
//   2. Local xcconfig — copy this file and fill in your Team ID:
//        cp Signing.example.xcconfig Signing.local.xcconfig
//      then reference it from project.yml `configFiles:` (see docs) or set the
//      value directly in your local checkout. Signing.local.xcconfig is
//      gitignored so your Team ID is never committed.
//
// Your Apple Developer Team ID is the 10-character identifier shown in the
// Apple Developer portal (Membership) — e.g. ABCDE12345.

DEVELOPMENT_TEAM =
